-- Ghana, Mali Complete Semifinals Lineup at Soccer’s Africa Cup of Nations
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-02-06T00:59:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/ghana-mali-complete-semifinals-lineup-at-soccer-s-africa-cup-of-nations.html
Ghana  beat Tunisia 2-1 after extra
time to reach the semifinals of soccer’s Africa Cup of Nations,
while Mali eliminated co-host Gabon in a penalty shootout.  Ghana’s Andre Ayew got the winning goal in the first period
of extra time yesterday in Franceville, Gabon, to set up a
final-four meeting with Zambia. Mali won 5-4 on penalties after
a 1-1 draw in Libreville and will face  Ivory Coast  for a place
in the championship match. The semifinals are scheduled for Feb.
8 with the final four days later.  Ghana, which secured the last of its four titles in
Africa’s biennial soccer championship in 1982, was beaten in the
final two years ago by record seven-time winner  Egypt .  In Libreville, Barcelona’s Seydou Keita got the decisive
spot kick for Mali, which achieved its best result in 1972 by
finishing as the runner-up.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Cone in London at 
